   "source": [
    "# Creating a PubMed Chatbot using Azure"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7ceedc61-32b6-4cf6-a66c-5254632ec0d2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Overview  \n",
    "[PubMed](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/about/) supports the search and retrieval of biomedical and life sciences literature with the aim of improving health both globally and personally. Here we create a chatbot that is grounded on PubMed data. It is recommended to use the **AzureML** kernel in your Jupyter notebook.\"  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cf8e31b5-7eac-4dc6-a9e3-3da9249fa013",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Prerequisites  \n",
    "We assume you have access to both Azure OpenAI and have already deployed an LLM."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "94311c09-5a18-4e17-b601-cbec160f2c7c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Get started"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f16f8947-ed11-4e59-a9c4-bb7cf6a11221",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this tutorial we will be using Azure OpenAI which (if you havent already) you can learn how to deploy [here](https://github.com/STRIDES/NIHCloudLabAzure/blob/main/notebooks/GenAI/azure_infra_setup/README.md). This tutorial utilizes the model **gpt-5.4-nano** and the embeddings model **text-embedding-3-small**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f8f82f35-13b1-4d37-80e6-3745a13ab2df",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Our chatbot will rely on documents to answer our questions to do so we are supplying it a **vector index**. A vector index or index is a data structure that enables fast and accurate search and retrieval of vector embeddings from a large dataset of objects. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bbb5f600-32cd-410c-8d25-26065d5996a1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To initiate **jupyter notebook**, you can learn it [here](https://github.com/STRIDES/NIHCloudLabAzure/blob/main/notebooks/GenAI/initiate_jupyter_notebook/InitiateJupyterNotebook.md). "
   ]
  },
  {
