   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For Azure OpenAI endpoint, click rectangle under **Azure OpenAI endpoint**. It would copy OpenAI endpoint, replace it in below cell with **your_openai_endpoint**\n",
    "\n",
    "For Azure OpenAI Key, click rectangle under **API key**. It would copy OpenAI key, replace it in below cell with **yourOpenAIKey**\n",
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "5544c268-cba4-4276-8375-cae54b243c07",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# configure environment\n",
    "import os, time, json, numpy as np, pandas as pd\n",
    "from typing import List, Dict\n",
    "from xml.etree import ElementTree as ET\n",
    "from openai import OpenAI\n",
    "import requests\n",
    "\n",
    "AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT=\"your_openai_endpoint\"\n",
    "AZURE_OPENAI_KEY = \"yourOpenAIKey\"\n",
    "AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_EMBED =  \"text-embedding-3-small\"\n",
    "AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_CHAT =  \"gpt-5.4-nano\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "EUTILS = \"https://eutils.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/\"\n",
    "EMAIL = 'your_nih_email_address'\n",
    "TOOL = 'pubmed-rag'\n",
    "IDCONV = \"https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/tools/idconv/api/v1/articles/\"\n",
    "\n",
    "client = OpenAI(base_url=AZURE_OPENAI_ENDPOINT, api_key=AZURE_OPENAI_KEY)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c574fcc4-621e-4225-b306-a8c08ea8d13a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Downloading interest of PubMed articles"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "af9070d1-79ff-49c9-acda-8a1d8249bf5f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "AWS marketplace has PubMed database named **PubMed Central® (PMC)** that contains free full-text archive of biomedical and life sciences journal article at the U.S. National Institutes of Health's National Library of Medicine (NIH/NLM). We will be using this database to fetch PubMed articles. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "12ef2ba0-eaae-49d3-bca2-9c7d8dff7d43",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Here we are downloading our interest of PubMed IDs from the NCBI E-Utilities and converting PubMed IDs to PMC IDs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "d90dc97c-2670-4f0e-adf6-e8f40d2e03f6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# ----------------------------\n",
    "# Rate limiting\n",
    "# ----------------------------\n",
    "def throttle_sleep():\n",
    "    # 3 rps default; ~10 rps with NCBI API key\n",
    "    time.sleep(0.34)\n",
    "# ----------------------------\n",
    "# Entrez search \n",
    "# ----------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "def esearch_pubmed(term: str, retmax: int = 500):\n",
    "    params = {\n",
    "        'db': 'pubmed',\n",
    "        'term': term,\n",
    "        'retmax': retmax,\n",
    "        'tool': TOOL,\n",
    "        'email': EMAIL\n",
    "    }\n",
    "    r = requests.get(EUTILS + 'esearch.fcgi', params=params)\n",
    "    r.raise_for_status()\n",
    "    throttle_sleep()\n",
    "    root = ET.fromstring(r.text)\n",
    "    pmids = [x.text for x in root.findall('.//IdList/Id')]\n",
    "    return pmids\n",
    "\n",
    "# PMIDs → PMCIDs (PMC ID Converter API)\n",
    "# ----------------------------\n",
    "def pmid_to_pmcids(pmids: List[str]) -> List[str]:\n",
    "    out = []\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(pmids), 200):\n",
    "        batch = \",\".join(pmids[i:i+200])\n",
    "        params = {\"ids\": batch, \"idtype\": \"pmid\", \"format\": \"json\", \"tool\": TOOL, \"email\": EMAIL}\n",
    "        r = requests.get(IDCONV, params=params, timeout=60)\n",
    "        r.raise_for_status(); throttle_sleep()\n",
    "        data = r.json()\n",
    "        for rec in data.get(\"records\", []):\n",
    "            if rec.get(\"pmcid\"):\n",
    "                out.append(rec[\"pmcid\"].upper())\n",
    "    # unique, preserve order\n",
    "    return list(dict.fromkeys(out))\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3ec7d0d1-b0d0-41f8-a036-0ced9fc429ba",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We are using boto3 library to connect to the public AWS s3 bucket where the metadata and full PubMed articles are stored."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "1923eb41-5044-4350-a00b-12a185b0aa65",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Fetch PMC full text with boto3\n",
    "\n",
    "import boto3\n",
    "from botocore import UNSIGNED\n",
    "from botocore.config import Config\n",
    "\n",
    "s3 = boto3.client( \"s3\", region_name=\"us-east-1\", config=Config(signature_version=UNSIGNED))\n",
    "BUCKET = \"pmc-oa-opendata\"\n",
    "\n",
    "def fetch_pmc_text(pmcid: str, max_version: int = 5) -> str | None:\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Updated 2026 PMC Cloud Service layout:\n",
    "      s3://pmc-oa-opendata/PMC<id>.<version>/PMC<id>.<version>.txt\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    pmc = pmcid.upper().strip().replace(\"PMC\", \"\")\n",
    "    for v in range(1, max_version + 1):\n",
    "        key = f\"PMC{pmc}.{v}/PMC{pmc}.{v}.txt\"\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            obj = s3.get_object(Bucket=BUCKET, Key=key)\n",
    "            data = obj[\"Body\"].read().decode(\"utf-8\")\n",
    "            if data.strip():\n",
    "                return data\n",
    "        except s3.exceptions.NoSuchKey:\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        except Exception as e:\n",
    "            print(f\"Error fetching {key}: {e}\")\n",
    "            continue\n",
    "    return None"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f248056c-a747-475f-a31d-8c5dc5dbc50d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Splitting our documents"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a5ec3a85-d338-49bd-be7e-1b8369b0e6e6",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Splitting our data into chucks will help our vector store parse through our data faster and efficiently.\n",
    "\n",
    "For this step we will be using langchains ***RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter***. This text splitter allows us to set the size of each chunk, if the chunks should have any text overlap (this is to help the model bridge some the chunks to make sense of them), and where best to separate texts. Each chunk will have the same metadata as the original document they came from."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f7c90bca-e062-4c73-a52d-20a8aabb2127",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "For our model to retrieve information from larger documents we need to split the text in our documents into smaller chucks. This will make it easier for our model to sift through our docs to retrieve information without going over the model's token limit."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cc3fb790-ccea-4220-80e4-6b60a0d07b94",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we will add metadata to our docs, split our docs into chunks, and embed them. Then much like for smaller documents we will create an index, the fields in our index will be different compared to the small document index."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "589b48c5-3b87-4238-b048-02a182dde5ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Split texts into chunks\n",
    "from langchain_text_splitters import RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter\n",
    "\n",
    "# Smaller chunks + overlap to avoid overly long inputs\n",
    "splitter = RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter(\n",
    "    chunk_size=1200,\n",
    "    chunk_overlap=100,\n",
    "    separators=[\"\\n\\n\", \"\\n\", \".\", \" \", \"\"]\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "MAX_LEN = 15000  # hard char cap per chunk (keeps embeddings safe)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_chunks(pmcids: List[str], limit: int = 60) -> List[Dict[str,str]]:\n",
    "    items = []\n",
    "    for pmc in pmcids[:limit]:\n",
    "        raw = fetch_pmc_text(pmc)\n",
    "        if not raw: \n",
    "            continue\n",
    "        for chunk in splitter.split_text(raw):\n",
    "            if len(chunk) > MAX_LEN:\n",
    "                # slice very long strings into safe pieces\n",
    "                for i in range(0, len(chunk), MAX_LEN):\n",
    "                    items.append({\"pmcid\": pmc, \"content\": chunk[i:i+MAX_LEN]})\n",
    "            else:\n",
    "                items.append({\"pmcid\": pmc, \"content\": chunk})\n",
    "    return items\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a6adb9a7-271f-4937-b2c0-0e385d27e6ff",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Generate embeddings (vectors)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3b8aee00-0a6d-49b9-b1b6-b3ea64620a2f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Embedding means that we are converting our text into a numerical vectors that will help our model find similar objects like documents that hold similar texts or find similar photos based on the numbers assigned to the object, basically capturing texts meaning and relationship through numbers. Depending on the model you choose you have to find an embedder that is compatible to our model. Since we are using a OpenAI model the compatible embedding model will be **text-embedding-3-small**."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "4bbe1513-ad49-49c0-8359-aaa45ef3c881",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# embed chunks and normalize it\n",
    "def embed_texts_batch(texts: List[str], batch_size: int = 100) -> List[List[float]]:\n",
    "    out = []\n",
    "    for i in range(0, len(texts), batch_size):\n",
    "        r = client.embeddings.create(\n",
    "            model=AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_EMBED,\n",
    "            input=texts[i:i+batch_size]\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        out.extend([row.embedding for row in r.data])\n",
    "    return out\n",
    "\n",
    "def normalize(vecs: List[List[float]]) -> List[List[float]]:\n",
    "    arr = np.asarray(vecs, dtype=\"float32\")\n",
    "    norms = np.linalg.norm(arr, axis=1, keepdims=True) + 1e-12\n",
    "    return (arr / norms).tolist()\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8b713be1-ddc3-49cc-a14a-13b4e4f86508",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Build FAISS from precomputed vectors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7955b8ff-9401-4024-a6f3-e5aeddc371da",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We pass from_embeddings(text_embeddings, embedding) with a tiny adapter so ***FAISS*** can embed the query text at search time using the same Azure embeddings deployment."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "9721a275-ff81-46e7-8e7b-2979b28467c5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Build FAISS index\n",
    "\n",
    "from langchain_community.vectorstores import FAISS\n",
    "\n",
    "class AzureQueryEmbedding:\n",
    "  \n",
    "    def embed_query(self, text: str):\n",
    "        r = client.embeddings.create(\n",
    "            model=AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_EMBED,  \n",
    "            input=text\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        vec = r.data[0].embedding\n",
    "        # normalize\n",
    "        arr = np.asarray([vec], dtype=\"float32\")\n",
    "        norms = np.linalg.norm(arr, axis=1, keepdims=True) + 1e-12\n",
    "        return (arr / norms)[0].tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "    def __call__(self, text: str):\n",
    "        return self.embed_query(text)\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "# when building FAISS (positional args only):\n",
    "query_embedding = AzureQueryEmbedding()\n",
    "\n",
    "def build_faiss(corpus: List[Dict[str,str]]) -> FAISS:\n",
    "    clean = [it for it in corpus if isinstance(it, dict) and \"content\" in it and \"pmcid\" in it]\n",
    "    docs_text = [it[\"content\"] for it in clean]\n",
    "    docs_meta = [{\"pmcid\": it[\"pmcid\"]} for it in clean]\n",
    "\n",
    "    vectors = normalize(embed_texts_batch(docs_text))\n",
    "\n",
    "    text_embeddings = list(zip(docs_text, vectors))  # [(text, vector), ...]\n",
    "    vs = FAISS.from_embeddings(text_embeddings, query_embedding)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # attach metadata\n",
    "    for i, md in enumerate(docs_meta):\n",
    "        doc_id = vs.index_to_docstore_id[i]\n",
    "        vs.docstore._dict[doc_id].metadata = md\n",
    "    return vs\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9a005526-d754-48d2-b866-1e0938b264ba",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Retrieval and Azure Chat answer with PMCID citations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ede00df1-39bf-4183-8532-eb06fe3e1914",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# OpenAI client to answer question\n",
    "\n",
    "SYSTEM_PROMPT = (\n",
    "    \"You are a biomedical assistant. Use ONLY the provided context. \"\n",
    "    \"If the context is insufficient, say you don't know. \"\n",
    "    \"Include PMCID citations in parentheses.\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "def format_ctx(docs: List[Document]) -> str:\n",
    "    return \"\\n\\n\".join([f\"(PMCID: {d.metadata.get('pmcid','PMC?')})\\n{d.page_content}\" for d in docs])\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def answer_with_azure(faiss_store: FAISS, question: str, k: int = 6) -> str:\n",
    "    ctx_docs = faiss_store.similarity_search(question, k=k)\n",
    "    ctx = format_ctx(ctx_docs)\n",
    "    resp = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "        model=AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_CHAT,\n",
    "        messages=[\n",
    "            {\"role\":\"system\",\"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n",
    "            {\"role\":\"user\",\"content\": f\"Question: {question}\\n\\nContext:\\n{ctx}\\n\\nAnswer (with PMCID citations):\"}\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        temperature=0.2,\n",
    "        max_completion_tokens=512\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return resp.choices[0].message.content"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "41508a5b-08ea-42cc-b937-aed42ed3601f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Zero-shot prompting  \n",
    "\n",
    "Zero-shot prompting does not require any additional training, but rather it asks a pre-trained language model to respond directly to a prompt, similar to if you were to ask Chat GPT a quick question without context. The model relies on its general language understanding and the patterns it has learned during its training to produce relevant output. In our script we grounded our model via a retriever to make sure it gathers information from our input data (PubMed).\n",
    "\n",
    "See below that the task is more like instructions notifying our model they will be asked questions which it will answer based on the info of the scientific documents provided from the index provided. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "39edf266-b21a-4690-9870-2df76d0fb771",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "from langchain_core.documents import Document\n",
    "\n",
    "def format_ctx(docs: List[Document]) -> str:\n",
    "    return \"\\n\\n\".join([f\"(PMCID: {d.metadata.get('pmcid','PMC?')})\\n{d.page_content}\" for d in docs])\n",
    "\n",
    "# zero-shot prompting\n",
    "\n",
    "SYSTEM_PROMPT = (\n",
    "    \"You are a biomedical assistant. Use ONLY the provided context. \"\n",
    "    \"If the context is insufficient, say you don't know. \"\n",
    "    \"Include PMCID citations in parentheses.\"\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "def answer_zero_shot(faiss_store: FAISS, question: str, k: int = 6) -> str:\n",
    "    ctx_docs = faiss_store.similarity_search(question, k=k)\n",
    "    ctx = format_ctx(ctx_docs)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    resp = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "        model=AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_CHAT,\n",
    "        messages=[\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{ctx}\\n\\nQuestion: {question}\\n\\nAnswer:\"}\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        temperature=0.2,\n",
    "        max_completion_tokens=512\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return resp.choices[0].message.content"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b4254e3e-3d56-41f0-a464-5271f878a1a0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### One-shot and Few-shot Prompting  \n",
    "\n",
    "One and few-shot prompting are similar to one-shot prompting, in addition to giving our model a task just like before we have also supplied an example of how we want the model to respond."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "df872ac0-1d30-4579-8d03-6bb544b3b26f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# one-shot prompting\n",
    "\n",
    "def answer_one_shot(faiss_store: FAISS, question: str, k: int = 6) -> str:\n",
    "    ctx_docs = faiss_store.similarity_search(question, k=k)\n",
    "    ctx = format_ctx(ctx_docs)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Static example interaction\n",
    "    example_context = \"(PMCID: PMC4455889)\\nThe two most significant risk factors for breast cancer are being female and advancing age, with the majority of cases diagnosed in women over 50.\"\n",
    "    example_question = \"What are the main risk factors for breast cancer?\"\n",
    "    example_answer = \"The primary risk factors for breast cancer are biological sex (being female) and increasing age, as most diagnoses occur in individuals over the age of 50 (PMC4455889).\"\n",
    "\n",
    "    resp = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "        model=AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_CHAT,\n",
    "        messages=[\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # --- ONE-SHOT EXAMPLE START ---\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{example_context}\\n\\nQuestion: {example_question}\\n\\nAnswer:\"},\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": example_answer},\n",
    "            # --- ONE-SHOT EXAMPLE END ---\n",
    "            \n",
    "            # Actual retrieved RAG payload\n",
    "            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{ctx}\\n\\nQuestion: {question}\\n\\nAnswer:\"}\n",
    "        ],\n",
    "        temperature=0.2,\n",
    "        max_completion_tokens=512\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return resp.choices[0].message.content"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "88370a44-5273-4912-a377-693c318d14fb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# few-shot prompting\n",
    "\n",
    "def answer_few_shot(faiss_store: FAISS, question: str, k: int = 6) -> str:\n",
    "    ctx_docs = faiss_store.similarity_search(question, k=k)\n",
    "    ctx = format_ctx(ctx_docs)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # 1. Define high-quality examples\n",
    "    few_shot_messages = [\n",
    "        {\"role\": \"system\", \"content\": SYSTEM_PROMPT},\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Example 1: Basic symptoms and warning signs\n",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"role\": \"user\", \n",
    "            \"content\": \"Context:\\n(PMCID: PMC2233445)\\nCommon early warning signs of breast cancer include a painless lump or thickening in the breast tissue, changes to the skin texture like dimpling, or spontaneous nipple discharge.\\n\\nQuestion: What are some common early signs of breast cancer?\"\n",
    "        },\n",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"role\": \"assistant\", \n",
    "            \"content\": \"Common early signs include a painless lump or thickening in the breast, skin dimpling, or unexpected nipple discharge (PMC2233445).\"\n",
    "        },\n",
    "         # Example 2: Negative training (Enforcing the basic \"Use ONLY provided context\" rule)\n",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"role\": \"user\", \n",
    "            \"content\": \"Context:\\n(PMCID: PMC3344556)\\nBreast cancer can spread to other areas of the body when cancer cells enter the lymphatic system or the bloodstream.\\n\\nQuestion: What specific surgical procedures are used to remove a tumor?\"\n",
    "        },\n",
    "        {\n",
    "            \"role\": \"assistant\", \n",
    "            \"content\": \"I don't know. The provided context only explains how breast cancer cells travel through the lymph system or bloodstream (PMC3344556). It does not mention any specific surgical procedures.\"\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # 2. Append the actual live user payload to the end of the history\n",
    "    few_shot_messages.append(\n",
    "        {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": f\"Context:\\n{ctx}\\n\\nQuestion: {question}\\n\\nAnswer:\"}\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # 3. Call your Azure deployment\n",
    "    resp = client.chat.completions.create(\n",
    "        model=AZURE_OPENAI_DEPLOYMENT_CHAT,\n",
    "        messages=few_shot_messages,\n",
    "        temperature=0.2,\n",
    "        max_completion_tokens=512\n",
    "    )\n",
    "\n",
    "    return resp.choices[0].message.content"
   ]
  },
